---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Boys Middle School - SF Bay Area">
	<Header />
	<main>
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="hero-overlay"></div>
			<div class="hero-content">
				<h1>Boys Middle School</h1>
				<p class="hero-subtitle">A unique middle school (grade 5–8) program for boys</p>
				<p class="hero-location">SF Bay Area</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="intro">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="intro-content">
					<p class="intro-text">The Boys Middle School (BMS) is a proposed 5th through 8th grade boys' school in the San Francisco Bay Area.</p>
					<p class="intro-text">We believe that some boys are not well served by existing coeducational public and private schools. Our mission is to build a school that deliberately embraces boys' natural instincts — channeling their energy, curiosity, and competitiveness into deep learning, mastery, and confidence through achievement.</p>
					<p class="intro-text">Read on to know more. If still interested, contact us by filling in the <a href="/interested">interest form</a>.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="why" class="why-section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Why a Private Boys' Middle School?</h2>

				<div class="content-block">
					<h3>Schools Are Not Working for Some Boys</h3>
					<p>A growing body of research shows that boys begin to underperform girls across many academic and behavioral measures starting around early adolescence (≈ age 10). These patterns often persist into adulthood.</p>
					<p>We believe school environments are a major contributing factor. Many classrooms are not designed to meet the developmental needs of a large subset of boys — particularly during the middle school years.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="content-block">
					<h3>The "Girls in STEM" Effect — Applied to Boys</h3>
					<p>As a society, we correctly focus on creating environments where girls can thrive, especially in historically male-dominated fields like STEM.</p>
					<p>But there is a parallel issue that often goes unaddressed:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>In most K–8 schools, 80% or more of teachers are female (vs 50% in boys schools)</li>
						<li>Combined with co-ed dynamics, this can create learning environments that do not fully engage or motivate some boys</li>
					</ul>
					<p>As children enter adolescence, both boys and girls benefit from environments that align with their intrinsic motivations. For some students, that environment is best provided by a single-sex school.</p>
					<blockquote>
						"Boys' schools embrace the intellectual, physical, social, and emotional lives of boys and appreciate the intensity and complexity of boyhood."
						<cite>— International Boys' School Coalition</cite>
					</blockquote>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="model" class="model-section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>The BMS Model - How BMS is different</h2>

				<div class="philosophy">
					<h3>Our Philosophy</h3>
					<p>We embrace the strengths of traditional boys' schools — discipline, grit, accountability, and respect.</p>
					<p class="core-belief">Our core belief is simple: <strong>When boys are genuinely motivated, they will work hard — and mastery follows.</strong></p>
				</div>

				<div class="model-card">
					<div class="model-number">1</div>
					<h3>Embracing Boys' Natural Interests</h3>
					<p class="model-subtitle">(Our Biggest Difference)</p>

					<h4>STEM Learning, Done Differently</h4>
					<p>Examples of how we approach STEM:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Taking apart and rebuilding everyday objects (bikes, engines, tools, clocks)</li>
						<li>Learning statistics and probability through sports analytics and games</li>
						<li>Field trips to construction sites, workshops, and industrial environments</li>
						<li>Visits and demonstrations from tradespeople, engineers, and parents</li>
						<li>Creating a competitive but fun environment boys enjoy being part of</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Humanities with Purpose and Rigor</h4>
					<p>Examples of our humanities approach:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Reading biographies of explorers, inventors, warriors, and statesmen</li>
						<li>Memorizing and reciting speeches, poetry, and historical texts</li>
						<li>Writing persuasive essays, battle reports, and strategic analyses</li>
						<li>Structured debates that teach logic, clarity, and respectful disagreement</li>
						<li>Civics taught through mock trials, councils, and governing bodies</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="goal-text">Our goal is to build both hard skills and soft skills — computation and grammar alongside rhetoric, judgment, and leadership.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="model-card">
					<div class="model-number">2</div>
					<h3>Mastery-Based Learning</h3>

					<h4>Why Mastery Matters</h4>
					<p>In most schools, entire classes move at the same pace. This leaves some students behind — and others bored.</p>
					<p><strong>At BMS:</strong></p>
					<ul>
						<li>Foundational skills must be fully mastered</li>
						<li>Student cohorts progress according to mastery cohorts where possible</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Math: A True Foundation</h4>
					<p><strong>We believe:</strong></p>
					<ul>
						<li>Math fundamentals must be mastered deeply</li>
						<li>All students should be ready for Geometry by high school</li>
						<li>Faster or broader advancement is welcome — with equal support</li>
					</ul>
					<p><strong>Our model:</strong></p>
					<ul>
						<li>Motivate concepts with real-world problems</li>
						<li>Assign lectures and practice via mastery platforms</li>
						<li>Prove mastery live, on paper, with a teacher, so the teacher can see how students think</li>
						<li>Teach others — including younger students</li>
					</ul>
					<blockquote>
						"If you can't explain it to someone else, you don't yet understand it yourself."
						<cite>— Richard Feynman</cite>
					</blockquote>
					<p>All mastery is ultimately verified offline, with pencil and paper.</p>

					<h4>Humanities: Traditional Skills, Taken Seriously</h4>
					<p>We want students to:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Communicate clearly and confidently</li>
						<li>Read deeply and write well</li>
						<li>Engage thoughtfully with ideas — classical and modern</li>
					</ul>
					<p>While humanities don't yet have a perfect mastery platform, we emphasize deliberate practice, feedback, and real performance.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="model-card">
					<div class="model-number">3</div>
					<h3>Family-Driven Personalization</h3>
					<p>Core academics can be completed in roughly 15 hours of focused work per week.</p>
					<p><strong>At BMS:</strong></p>
					<ul>
						<li>Students who need more time get it</li>
						<li>Students who are on track gain flexibility</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Instead of filling the day with science facts and arts and craft projects, families can choose how some time is used:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Advanced academics or tutoring</li>
						<li>Music practice or language learning</li>
						<li>Woodworking, maker lab, arts & crafts</li>
						<li>Reading, chess, board games</li>
						<li>Outdoor play and peer connection</li>
						<li>Teacher-guided passion projects</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="schedule">
						<div class="schedule-item">
							<h5>Mornings:</h5>
							<p>Focused core academics</p>
						</div>
						<div class="schedule-item">
							<h5>Afternoons:</h5>
							<p>Flexible, personalized time</p>
						</div>
						<div class="schedule-item">
							<h5>Outcome:</h5>
							<p>Your child gets their evenings and family time back.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="expectations" class="expectations">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>What You Can Expect</h2>
				<div class="expectations-grid">
					<div class="expectation-card">
						<h3>No Smartphones</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Phones are checked in for the entire day</li>
							<li>Students remain present mentally, physically, and socially</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="expectation-card">
						<h3>Tech Boundaries</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>All student tech activity is monitored and restricted</li>
							<li>Technology serves goals—not entertainment</li>
							<li>AI tools are used intentionally to support learning</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="expectation-card">
						<h3>Parent Participation</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Parents are warmly welcome (but not expected)</li>
							<li>Opportunities to give guest talks, assist with projects, drop in for afternoon sessions</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="expectation-card">
						<h3>School Environment</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Open-plan main area with activity zones</li>
							<li>Dedicated classrooms and maker labs</li>
							<li>Outdoor play space with sports equipment</li>
							<li>A culture of movement, collaboration, and exploration</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="cta-section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="cta-content">
					<h2>Interested?</h2>
					<p>Please fill out our short form and we will get back to you.</p>
					<a href="/interested" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Express Your Interest</a>
					<div class="cta-links">
						<a href="/about">Meet Our Founders</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		min-height: calc(100vh - 200px);
	}

	.container {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 2rem;
	}

	.hero {
		position: relative;
		background-image: url('/main.avif');
		background-size: cover;
		background-position: center;
		color: white;
		padding: 8rem 2rem;
		text-align: center;
		min-height: 500px;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
	}

	.hero-overlay {
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		right: 0;
		bottom: 0;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(10, 10, 11, 0.7) 0%, rgba(19, 19, 20, 0.85) 100%);
	}

	:global(html.light) .hero-overlay {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(253, 246, 227, 0.75) 0%, rgba(238, 232, 213, 0.85) 100%);
	}

	.hero-content {
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.hero h1 {
		color: white;
		font-size: 3.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.1;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	:global(html.light) .hero h1 {
		color: var(--color-primary);
	}

	.hero-subtitle {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		opacity: 0.95;
		line-height: 1.4;
	}

	:global(html.light) .hero-subtitle,
	:global(html.light) .hero-location {
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	.hero-location {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	.intro {
		padding: 3rem 0;
		background: var(--color-bg);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.intro-content {
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.intro-text {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.intro-text:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.btn {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
		border-radius: 6px;
		font-weight: 600;
		transition: all 0.3s ease;
		border: 1px solid transparent;
		cursor: pointer;
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}

	.btn-primary {
		background: var(--color-accent);
		color: var(--color-text-dark);
		border-color: var(--color-accent);
	}

	.btn-primary:hover {
		background: var(--color-accent-hover);
		border-color: var(--color-accent-hover);
		transform: translateY(-2px);
		box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(217, 119, 87, 0.25);
	}

	.btn-large {
		padding: 1rem 2.5rem;
		font-size: 1.125rem;
	}

	.why-section {
		padding: 3rem 0;
		background: var(--color-bg-light);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.why-section h2 {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.content-block {
		background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
		padding: 2.5rem;
		border-radius: 12px;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		transition: all 0.3s ease;
	}

	.content-block:hover {
		border-color: var(--color-accent);
		transform: translateY(-2px);
	}

	.content-block h3 {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		font-size: 1.75rem;
	}

	.content-block p {
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
	}

	.content-block ul {
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
		padding-left: 2rem;
	}

	.content-block li {
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
	}

	blockquote {
		border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
		padding: 1.5rem;
		margin: 2rem 0;
		background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
		font-style: italic;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	blockquote cite {
		display: block;
		margin-top: 1rem;
		font-style: normal;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--color-accent);
	}

	.model-section {
		padding: 3rem 0;
		background: var(--color-bg);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.model-section h2 {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.philosophy {
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto 3rem;
		text-align: center;
		padding: 2.5rem;
		background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
		border-radius: 12px;
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.philosophy h3 {
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.philosophy p {
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.core-belief {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		color: var(--color-accent) !important;
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
	}

	.model-card {
		background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 3rem;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		position: relative;
		transition: all 0.3s ease;
	}

	.model-card:hover {
		border-color: var(--color-accent);
		transform: translateY(-2px);
	}

	.model-number {
		position: absolute;
		top: -20px;
		left: 3rem;
		background: var(--color-accent);
		color: var(--color-text-dark);
		width: 48px;
		height: 48px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(217, 119, 87, 0.3);
	}

	.model-card h3 {
		font-size: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		margin-top: 0.5rem;
	}

	.model-subtitle {
		color: var(--color-accent);
		font-style: italic;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		font-size: 1.125rem;
	}

	.model-card h4 {
		color: var(--color-accent);
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
	}

	.model-card p {
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.model-card ul {
		margin: 1rem 0 2rem;
		padding-left: 2rem;
	}

	.model-card li {
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
	}

	.goal-text {
		font-weight: 500;
		color: var(--color-text) !important;
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
	}

	.schedule {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
		padding: 2rem;
		background: var(--color-bg);
		border-radius: 8px;
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.schedule-item h5 {
		color: var(--color-accent);
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.schedule-item p {
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.expectations {
		padding: 3rem 0;
		background: var(--color-bg-light);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.expectations .container {
		max-width: 1400px;
	}

	.expectations h2 {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	.expectations-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
		gap: 2rem;
	}

	.expectation-card {
		background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
		padding: 2.5rem;
		border-radius: 12px;
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		transition: all 0.3s ease;
	}

	.expectation-card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-4px);
		border-color: var(--color-accent);
	}

	.expectation-card h3 {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	.expectation-card ul {
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
	}

	.expectation-card li {
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
	}

	.cta-section {
		background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
		border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		color: var(--color-text);
		padding: 4rem 0;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.cta-content h2 {
		color: var(--color-text);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.cta-content p {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
	}

	.cta-links {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
	}

	.cta-links a {
		color: var(--color-accent);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: all 0.3s ease;
	}

	.cta-links a:hover {
		color: var(--color-accent-hover);
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	@media (max-width: 1024px) {
		.expectations-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.hero {
			padding: 5rem 1.5rem;
			min-height: 400px;
		}

		.hero h1 {
			font-size: 2.5rem;
		}

		.hero-subtitle {
			font-size: 1.25rem;
		}

		.hero-location {
			font-size: 1.125rem;
		}

		.intro {
			padding: 2rem 0;
		}

		.intro-text {
			font-size: 1rem;
		}

		.why-section, .model-section, .expectations {
			padding: 2rem 0;
		}

		.content-block, .model-card {
			padding: 1.5rem;
		}

		.model-number {
			left: 1.5rem;
		}

		.model-card h3 {
			font-size: 1.5rem;
		}

		.schedule {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			padding: 1.5rem;
		}

		.expectations-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 1.5rem;
		}

		.cta-section {
			padding: 2rem 0;
		}

		.container {
			padding: 0 1rem;
		}
	}
</style>

